text: Medical Lake is a city in Spokane County, Washington. The population was 4,874 at the 2020 census. Medical Lake has a psychiatric hospital named Eastern State Hospital. ==History== The city of Medical Lake was founded in 1890. The city is named after a nearby lake. The Spokane Native American tribe which lived in the area for a long time, thought the water from the lake could heal sickness and injuries. White settlers who moved to the area in the 1870s, sold salts from the lake as medicine. == References == Category:Cities in Washington (state) Category:Spokane County, Washington
